The market for antispasmodics drugs is segmented based on drug type, application, and distribution channel. In terms of drug type, the market is categorized into hyoscyamine, dicyclomine, scopolamine, and others. These drugs are commonly used to relieve muscle spasms and are effective in treating conditions such as irritable bowel syndrome and urinary incontinence. In the application segment, antispasmodics drugs are utilized for gastrointestinal disorders, neurological disorders, and other indications. Additionally, the distribution channels through which these drugs are accessed include hospital pharmacies, retail pharmacies, and online pharmacies. The ease of availability through various channels contributes to the market growth and accessibility of these drugs to consumers.

